column4: <content>Good Shepherd (Glück 44 & 80). Transparency: Paint apparently very thin (overcleaned?) white [?] the [?] of the wolf. The greenish landscape on left too soft for P.B.I. Underpainting only? (but the landscape with bird trap was a similar heavy background). The path on the right typical of late lost ? pictures. The brushes cf. Spencer Churchill Wedding Procession. Unfinished? The delicacy of the execution Jan B.? This version certainly not by P.B.II.</content>
